IMPARTIALITY IN political journalism is under scrutiny as never before. President Trump took a trademark pop at the “fakers” when he resumed his campaign rallies in Tulsa. Meanwhile the White House has begun decapitating state-funded global news agencies like Voice of America. Can fair-minded reporting survive hyper-partisan politics? John Prideaux, The Economist’s US editor, hosts with Charlotte Howard, New York bureau chief, and Washington correspondent Jon Fasman. Runtime: 39 min  Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn For access to The Economist’s print, digital and audio editions subscribe: economist.com/2020electionpod